<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-569-219  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 569 219.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Nov 5 1990 v7 n44 p48(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sandamp;H unveiling multiuser system to Windows 3.0. (Sandamp;H ComputerSystems Inc. preparing to open multiuser operating system toWindows 3.0 by introducing new TSX-32 operating system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sherer, Paul M.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   S and H Computer Systems Inc. (Product enhancement).andO;Product:   TSX-32 (Operating system) (Product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Multiuser MicrocomputersEnhancementsOS-2.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Paul M. ShererandM;Sandamp;H Computer Systems Inc. is preparing to open its multiuser operatingsystems to Windows 3.0.andM;The Nashville, Tenn., firm will announce at Comdex/Fall the November shipmentof a new version of its TSX-32 operating system that lets as many as eightusers on PC or dumb terminals run Windows 3.0 applications on a 386 or 486host PC simultaneously.andP;  TSX-32 version 3.0 supports up to 64 users from onehost, connected via Ethernet cabling.andP;  It gives each DOS program 640K bytesof memory, and gives each user as many as 10 concurrent, multitasking DOSsessions.andM;Version 3.0 makes access to large files as much as 12 times faster than underDOS by keeping both the directory list and commonly used parts of the DOSfile allocation table in memory rather than on disk, company officials said.andM;Version 3.0 sells for $1,450, including one year of support and updates.andM;Sandamp;H can be contacted at (615) 327-3670.andO;</TEXT></DOC>